en_content:
Splendor of the lilies of May, you are our Queen,
the dawn of our eyes, the peace of our evening;
and we place in you all our blue heavens of hope,
our laughter and our hearts and all our sorrow.

We will gather for you, amiable sovereign,
flowers and Hail Marys all along the way;
and if the shadow of evening obscures the morning,
pierce with gold and azure the wall of our sorrow.

Whiteness of the lilies of May, Virgin beautiful and serene;
take us by the hand when evening comes;
take us by the hand along our sorrow.

Sovereign from the beginning,
hear my prayer;
my soul, my heart thirst for You;
my gaze longs to see You
and I look to no other,
for there is no god comparable to You;
nothing is as great as You
since You alone are wondrously great;
therefore, gather the nations
so that they may give thanks
and praise Your Holy Name
around a single Tabernacle;
may they offer Your Sacrifice to our Father
in heaven, with one voice and
in the same Spirit;
Guardian of our soul,
wonderfully strong,
invincible,
may Your whole creation
serve You in the Most Holy Trinity;
grant us this blessing;

Amen.

Adorable, terrible, blessed, give Him to us;
send forth your Spirit and all shall be created,
and you shall renew the face of the earth;
for it is not in the deluge of many waters,
in the trouble and confusion of such diverse affections,
that one draws near to God;
lead the Spirit upon the earth:
let the sea recede and let the dry land appear
which thirsts for the fountain of life.
Let the dove come with the olive branch, announcing peace.
